╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 6.1: Regex Select                     ║
║  Category: Multi-Selection         Difficulty: ★★☆ Intermediate  ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  s     Select all regex matches within the current selection
  c     Change (delete selection and enter insert mode)

This is the KILLER feature of Helix. Instead of :%s/old/new/g,
you select text, split it into sub-selections, and edit them all
simultaneously with multiple cursors — live.

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  The paragraph below uses "color" five times. You need to change
  every instance to "colour" (British spelling) — all at once.

  The Helix way:
  1. Select the entire practice block (use x to select lines, or
     position before the first line and v then j to extend)
  2. Press  s  — a prompt appears at the bottom
  3. Type   color   and press Enter
     → All five instances are now individual selections!
  4. Press  c  — all five are deleted, you're in insert mode
     at every cursor simultaneously
  5. Type   colour
  6. Press  Esc  — done. Five replacements, zero repetition.

  Feel the power. This is multi-cursor editing driven by regex,
  and it works on ANY pattern.

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

The color of the sky changes throughout the day. At dawn, a warm
color spreads across the horizon. By noon the color shifts to a
brilliant blue. Artists know that color theory is essential for
painting realistic scenes. The right color can set the entire
mood of a composition.

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

The colour of the sky changes throughout the day. At dawn, a warm
colour spreads across the horizon. By noon the colour shifts to a
brilliant blue. Artists know that colour theory is essential for
painting realistic scenes. The right colour can set the entire
mood of a composition.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Make sure your selection covers ALL five lines before
          pressing s. Use x repeatedly or v + j.
  Hint 2: After pressing s, type "color" (not "colour") and Enter.
          You should see 5 selections highlighted.
  Hint 3: Press c (not d!) — this deletes and enters insert mode.
          Then type "colour" and all five update at once.
  Hint 4: If you only got some matches, your initial selection
          probably didn't cover all the text. Undo with u and
          make a bigger selection.
